BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Data for autonomous mobility in cities and smart traffic control -
  Live translation available in English.
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T153000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T170000
DESCRIPTION:Gain practical insights into the requirements of modern mobili
 ty infrastructures. How can we ensure both safety and efficiency in their 
 implementation? And what are the key technologies driving the smart mobili
 ty of the future? 
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital design of Leipzig's urban space – diGuRaL (not public)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T153000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T170000
LOCATION:Ratsplenarsaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Data handling in the Open Data Portal Hesse
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T110000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T113000
DESCRIPTION:In their joint presentation\, Eric Engels and Norman Radtke hi
 ghlight special features in the reuse of data catalogs from existing open 
 data portals (e.g. filtering for Hessian content)\, the expanded presentat
 ion of content\, the generation of statistical evaluations of data catalog
 s\, and the preparation of their own data catalogs (e.g.\, a partial data 
 catalog for each municipality). The focus of this work is strongly on data
  homogenization and standardization\, for example\, to enable alignment at
  the file level. The proposed solutions are implemented both within the CK
 AN extension developed in Hesse itself and on the data of the knowledge gr
 aph (RDF\, DCAT)\, using SPARQL update queries.
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Publish confidential data securely and flexibly using the Cell Key
  method
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T113000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T120000
DESCRIPTION:Data sets containing personal and other confidential informati
 on are usually only published in summary form and with few subcategories. 
 The risk of confidential individual values being inferred from differences
  between different summaries is too great. The cell key method allows thes
 e data sets to be published flexibly without revealing confidential inform
 ation. The presentation introduces the cell key method and a software solu
 tion that supports the workflow for creating data sets modified using the 
 cell key method and also provides a user interface for publication.
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Urban Data Management Bonn – A change project with many dimensio
 ns
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T120000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T123000
DESCRIPTION:Since 2020\, the federal city of Bonn has been actively pursui
 ng a strategic approach to urban data. The presentation describes the late
 st active developments in the areas of technical development of an urban d
 ata platform based on the open source project Civitas Core\, the introduct
 ion of a data strategy and governance\, and activities to increase data li
 teracy in the administration and urban society. The aim of these activitie
 s is to achieve comprehensive data excellence in the handling of urban dat
 a.
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Autonomous shuttles: Data basis for intelligent on-demand mobility
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T153000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T160000
DESCRIPTION:Autonomous shuttles are key technologies for the mobility of t
 he future. But what data do they need to offer on-demand services efficien
 tly and safely? Based on many years of involvement in the ABSOLUT II proje
 ct\, this presentation provides practical insights into the data requireme
 nts and architectures of autonomous shuttle infrastructures.
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:AIAMO – Artificial Intelligence And MObility
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T160000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T163000
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Influencing Commuting Patterns Through Relevant Data: The Roles Th
 at Cities and Employers Can Play
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T163000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T170000
LOCATION:Sitzungssaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Building RDF Knowledge Graphs with eccenca Corporate Memory (condu
 cted by eccenca GmbH)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T110000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T123000
DESCRIPTION:Hands-on training: The journey of creating your own knowledge 
 graph. This session focuses on practical application: Using the Community 
 Edition Sandbox eccenca.my\, participants will set up their own instance o
 f eccenca Corporate Memory. \nThe practical session will focus on:\n- Buil
 ding and modeling knowledge graphs.\n- Effective visualisation of complex 
 data structures.\n- Transfer to practice with helpful self-study materials
 . \n\n(Please note that the training will be conducted in English)
LOCATION:Room 377
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Young people and AI – What they know and how they use it (conduc
 ted by Leipzig City Libraries)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T153000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T170000
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, we take a look at how AI is used by young p
 eople aged 12 to 16 from an educational perspective. We present how Leipzi
 g's municipal libraries are addressing the topic of AI together with schoo
 lchildren and what insights this has yielded for our educational work. We 
 discuss how the exchange with young people has opened up new perspectives 
 for us and what challenges and opportunities arise when dealing with AI.
LOCATION:Room 259
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:From satellite images to administrative decisions: Effective use o
 f geospatial and remote sensing data in local government
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T110000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T123000
LOCATION:Ratsplenarsaal
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Workshop on AIAMO – Artificial Intelligence And Mobility in Leip
 zig
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T110000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T123000
DESCRIPTION:To what extent can artificial intelligence and incentive measu
 res optimize mobility in a growing city like Leipzig—and what are the li
 mits of technical solutions? Starting from the current situation in the Le
 ipzig pilot region\, we will discuss specific scenarios together: from AI-
 supported traffic management at construction sites to behavioral changes d
 riven by incentive mechanisms in a mobility app.
LOCATION:Room 369
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:How generative artificial intelligence is changing work and study 
 (conducted by ScaDS.AI)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T133000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T150000
DESCRIPTION:Modern AI-driven chat apps such as ChatGPT\, Gemini\, Claude a
 nd others are changing the way we work unavoidably. For many\, this means 
 writing texts or programming more efficiently. Some people overestimate th
 e quality of generated text and may not admit that they have not curated A
 I-generated text properly. About 20 years ago we had to learn how to “go
 ogle” properly\, today we need to learn how to “prompt”. In this lec
 ture\, we will give an insight into various challenges that the current AI
  revolution is imposing on us and a number of opportunities in this contex
 t. The lecture gives examples\, tips and tricks for dealing with Generativ
 e AI and will be followed by a practical part. It is recommended that you 
 bring your own laptop to take part.
LOCATION:Room 377
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:DIPAS – Digital participation online and on site
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T133000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260602T150000
DESCRIPTION:Hands-on: Creation of your own DIPAS participation procedures 
 via the Drupal backend. The focus is on the technical design of participat
 ion procedures and their implementation in DIPAS\, as well as the creation
  of your own DIPAS_story (geodata storytelling).\n\n- Introduction to DIPA
 S by the speakers\n- Design and implementation of a participation process 
 (project admin)\n- Creation of a DIPAS_story
LOCATION:Room 270
END:VEVENT
