BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ideas Workshop: AI & Social Work (Booking requires a voucher)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260605T083000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260605T123000
DESCRIPTION:The Ideas Workshop is designed for professionals from all area
 s of social work who are looking for concrete ways to use AI effectively i
 n their daily work. The focus is on the specific needs and challenges of t
 he field: How can AI truly lighten the workload when resources are scarce?
  What are the obstacles\, and how can they be overcome? An interactive wor
 kshop for participation\, experimentation\, and networking: In the first p
 art\, concise presentations will provide inspiration regarding the current
  state of AI in social work. In the second part\, participants—with AI a
 s their co-pilot—will spend 90 minutes developing their own ideas: from 
 their specific challenges to the proposed solution and the appropriate fun
 ding strategy. \nAfterward\, a lunch buffet will provide an opportunity fo
 r networking and informal discussion across the presentations. Moderated b
 y Hannes Meinhardt / Social Impact. Free registration via roots@leipzig.de
 .
LOCATION:Smart City Lab
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Guided tour of the Smart City Lab
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260605T100000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260605T120000
DESCRIPTION:As an innovative experimental hub for the city government\, th
 e Smart City Lab Leipzig explores the potential of digital transformation 
 for the sustainable and citizen-friendly development of our city. Discover
  here how Leipzig is using smart technologies to make urban life more sust
 ainable and modern. The Smart City Lab is located at Magazingasse 3 in Lei
 pzig. 
LOCATION:Smart City Lab
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:KMI demonstrators
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260605T100000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260605T110000
DESCRIPTION:At the KMI Competence Center\, visitors can view and test demo
 nstrators. “The Agile Factory of the Future” provides a live demonstra
 tion of how Industry 5.0 works\, and the “DeNKI Demonstrator” helps vi
 sitors understand the implications and conflicting goals of AI use. Explor
 e here how AI can be used successfully and sustainably. The KMI demonstrat
 ors can be viewed and tested at the Institute for Applied Computer Science
  (Institut für Angewandte Informatik e.V.) on the 2nd floor at Goerdelerr
 ing 9 in Leipzig. 
LOCATION:KMI Demo-Raum
END:VEVENT
